	</script><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" vspace="0" hspace="0">
  <tr><td width="2" height="15"><img src="/lotr/gfx/center_column/1.gif" width="2" height="25"></td>
    <td width="700" background="/lotr/gfx/cloud/bluecc.gif" height="15" valign="bottom"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr><td><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font"><font color="#8989B1">Advanced Decks</font></B></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="2"></td><td valign="top"> 
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5"><tr><td><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font">Versatility of the Mirror V1.0</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.60)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21543">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8808">Will "Will Turner" Turner</A></FONT> <font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8808&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> This deck uses the mirror of Galadriel and Aragorn/Elrond to kill opponents.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> February 18, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Starting:<br>
Frodo, SOD<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(96)">The One Ring, Isildur&#39;s Bane</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(245)">Aragorn, King in Exile</a><br>
<br>
Free Peoples:<br>
4 Elrond<br>
2 Galadriel<br>
2 Celeborn<br>
3 Arwen<br>
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(260)">Legolas, Greenleaf</a><br>
1 Rangers sword<br>
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(256)">Gwemegil</a><br>
1 Galadriels Mirror<br>
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(247)">Defiance</a><br>
1 Last alliance of elves and men<br>
1 Tale of the Gil-Gilad<br>
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(304)">Athelas</a><br>
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(850)">One Whom Men Would Follow</a><br>
1 Saga of Elendil <br>
1 Orophin<br>
1 Rumil<br>
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(267)">The Seen and the Unseen</a><br>
4 <a href="javascript:card_browser(273)">Support of the Last Homely House</a><br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
4 Cave troll<br>
4 Goblin <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y<br>
4 Goblin scavenger<br>
4 <a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a><br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(86)">Moria Scout</a><br>
4 <a href="javascript:card_browser(72)">Goblin Runner</a><br>
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(78)">Goblin Swarms</a><br>
3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a><br>
2 Trolls keyward<br>
2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a><br>
1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(81)">Guard Commander</a><br>
<br>
Adventure deck:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(201)">East Road</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(212)">Ettenmoors</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(217)">Council Courtyard</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(226)">Moria Stairway</a><br>
The Bridge of Kaza-dum<br>
Lothlorien woods<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(234)">Silverlode Banks</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Ok, lets start with overall strategy. The goal of the deck is to keep a very small fellowship while still having the means to defend with cards like Elrond and Celeborn. This is done with SOTLHH. For an exert the allies can fight. Pretty simple. Some opponents might not see this coming. Since all the good allies heal themselves there&#39;s no need to pack 4 athelas like most decks are these days. With a +3 to power from Support, Elrond becomes a whopping 11 strength power house. And he&#39;s been doing it for hundreds of years, not bad for an old man. Celeborn is ok, he&#39;s got pretty high strength, just don&#39;t try using his ability until he&#39;s almost dead then putting him into an iffy battle. If you feel funny about the battle don&#39;t go into it unless you really need to. So with support cards like defiance Elrond and Celeborn will clean up the minions and heal next turn by themselves. Nothing like a free heal is there. <br>
<br>
Starting:<br>
I start standard frodo and Aragorn KIE. He&#39;s there so he can heal Arwen. See everyone can heal someone. <br>
<br>
Fellowship:<br>
I have two galadriel in there for healing celeborn and herself after using the mirror. She can exert a couple times if you time it right and make sure you get rid of minions. Remember that minion conditions aren&#39;t any good if the minions aren&#39;t there to use them. Legolas is there for spice, he can peg off a small vitality guy then sit back and laugh as Elrond takes an army on himself. Everything else is standard issue. Seen and unseen is for blade tip , black breath cheese. I have a couple remover cards(Cards that get rid of conditions) in the deck so by the time you get to site 9 they should be gone. The opponent only has so many blade tips right? With my luck they&#39;ll legalize 5 just against me. <br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
Standard moria swarm. Play cave troll as early as possible. That doesn&#39;t mean at all expenses. If opponent is using aimed archery then he&#39;ll have to exert a bunch of times so it evens out. It&#39;s like he did his damage anyway. Then when he moves again you can swarm. Another way I have caught opponents is making them exert for archery sacking an armory then because they are exausted and my minion is still alive they have to fight and now even if you do one wound they still die. Once you get one party member the rest should start to fall like a drunken teen at a rave party on exstacy. <br>
<br>
I&#39;ll go through an &quot;against&quot; section:<br>
<br>
Against Sauron: just fight, they have low strength and low vitality, it&#39;ll be hard for them to do anything against your 10-12 power guys.<br>
<br>
against goblins: use legolas to peg off a couple then fight the rest. with the mirror you can discard a couple if you get lucky enough.<br>
<br>
against nazgul: this is the toughest match up because of their fierce ability. Just fight and do your damage early, they shouldn&#39;t have too many out cause mostly you&#39;ll have 1-2 companions at one time but have allies to fight in your place so he can only play maybe 1 nazgul.<br>
<br>
against uruk: uruk are expensive, you don&#39;t give that much away. Just fight them all. If he gets down a few you can handle it with your legolas archery or arwen and aragorn fighting or elrond showing where they can shove those odd shaped swords.<br>
<br>
This deck has worked pretty good for me. The only time it loses is on a really bad run of cards. In that case, just ditch and draw. This deck almost always goes through every card before the end. If anyone has suggestions then tell me what you think I should change and why not just a card title. yeah, you know who you are. haha. It is a fun deck to play and I guess thats all that matters in the end but it does help to kick some hiney sometimes too.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21543"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21543" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
          <td width="1" valign="top"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="16" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
        </tr>
